The paper proposes a new approach to TDMA scheduling for wireless sensor networks (WSNs), which falls under the category of network protocols and algorithms. The paper discusses the trade-off between schedule length and scheduling time, which is related to optimization and control. The simulation results and theoretical analysis are used to evaluate the performance of the proposed approach, which falls under the category of performance evaluation. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Other possible sub-categories include cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.IT (Information Theory), as the paper involves optimization, control, and algorithm design.
